10:
I've got you, Kugui. We'll face this
together.
13: ...Why would you go so far for me?
16:
I'm pushing you into this. It's only fair
for me to share the burden.
20: No... It's fine. This is my sin to bear.
28: ...This is where I created the dragon.
30:
But what is the purpose of bringing
me here?
35:
I felt like I needed to see it with my
own two eyes... Otherwise my words
would never get through to you.
36:
Now I know. This is the source of guilt
that's been weighing on your
shoulders.
41:
My art will only ever hurt others. I
never wanted this power...
44: Then why don't you give it to me?
48:
...Excuse me? Even if I could, this
power isn't something to be taken
lightly!
50:
I won't deny that it can be
dangerous. But it also has the
potential to make dreams come
true.
53:
If you really want to give up art, then
I'll just paint in your place.
60: Guys! Can you help me set up?
63: Kugui, mind modeling for a painting?
70: What is the meaning of this?
77:
Yeah, this turned out pretty well.
Come look, Kugui!
86:
When I saw your art for the first time,
I knew... I wanted to paint like you.
88:
Seriously, everything I wanted to
create, you had already drawn
before me!
91:
So you imitated my style while
painting this?
94:
Ahaha... At my skill level, all I can do
is copy others. But I'll definitely build
up my own style one day.
96:
You see, my parents are merchants.
They were never home when I was a
kid, so I spent a lot of time playing
pretend... Imagining whatever I
wanted.
98:
Now I can turn my imaginations into
reality through art. That's why I paint.
99:
And you... You're the artist I wish I
could be, with your art skills and
your power.
103:
How can you say that... when you've
seen the destruction I've caused!
Look around you!
110:
I'll create, and I'll keep creating until I
can catch up to you.
113:
Which is why you need to keep
painting too. That's how we'll reach
new heights together.
116:
B-but... I could really, truly hurt
someone the next time I try!
118:
If you want to paint, then paint. Don't
deny the artist that you are.
121:
I'll even be your reason to keep
going, if you need me to be.
132:
I'm surprised. You can be rather
mean when you want to be.
136:
Hey, if my words hit you hard, then
that's proof you've got some pride
as an artist.
140:
I... I don't want to hear that from
someone who still has a long way to
go!
143:
Aw, meanie.
Did it bother you that much that I
copied you?
146:
Of course. My style is the result of
many years of work... It'd be more
surprising if I wasn't protective of it.
151:
Ahahaha! And to think you were
thinking of giving it all up!
156:
Oh, shush! Now you've made me
mad...
160:
Yeah? What's mad Kugui gonna do
about it?
166:
I can't paint like you do, with joy in
every stroke, but... I can devote
myself entirely to this piece.
170:
*giggle* Yeah, your art is really
something. I don't know how I'm
gonna catch up.
175:
Wh-why are you crying?! Did I...
paint something wrong?
179: No! I'm just so relieved, I...
183:
Painting with you is fun... I'm so glad
we got to do it again!
186:
Yes, it... it was not an unpleasant
experience.
189:
I was really scared, you know? About
you quitting art forever...
190:
I couldn't think of any other way to
convince you to keep going! I'm
sorry!
195:
Gah! Wh-what's wrong?! Don't tell
me you two ended up fighting!
199:
N-no, we were just about to make
up actually...
204:
...After everything that's happened, it
wouldn't do for me to run away any
longer.
